refreshment /rɪˈfrɛʃmənt/

(refreshments) 

1. N-PLURAL Refreshments are drinks and small amounts of food that are provided, for example, during a meeting or a trip. 茶点 

例： Lunch and refreshments will be provided. 将提供午餐和茶点。 

2. N-UNCOUNT You can refer to food and drink as refreshment . 食物和饮料 [正式] 

例： May I offer you some refreshment? 可以请您吃点喝点什么吗？

